==========LAMP (LINUX APACHE MYSQL PHP)======



==============================================

launch the linux machine  and install the apache

1)yum install httpd
2) systemctl start httpd
3) systemctl enable httpd
4) allow the 80 port number





=========================================
SQL

1) enable the EPEL for sql 

 yum localinstall https://dev.mysql.com/get/mysql80-community-release-el7-1.noarch.rpm

2) yum update
3) yum install mysql-community-server
4) systemctl start mysqld.service
5)systemctl enable mysqld.service
6)systemctl status mysqld.service
7) cd /var/logs/
   more mysqld.log
   copy the password
8) mysql_secure_installation   change the password
9) mysql -h localhost -u root -p      connect to sql data base
10) show databases;    check the data bases
11) create database wordpress    create database for the name of wordpress
    exit



======================================================

PHP (DRUPAL)

1)wget http://ftp.drupal.org/files/projects/drupal-7.31.tar.gz      downlaod package

2) tar -xf drupal-7.31.tar.gz     extarct the package    
    
    create a directory for the name of drupal in /var/www/html
	
        go to directory i.e  cd drupal /   and copy the files into /var/www/html/drupal

            cp -rvf * /var/www/html/drupal

edit the fonfiguration file   vi /etc/httpd/conf/httpf.conf
   replace index.php in place of index.html

3) open your browser and go the any of following links to begin installation  
		http://your-ip-address/drupal

4)To fix these above errors, run the following commands
		yum install php*
systemctl start httpd
mkdir -p /var/www/html/drupal/sites/default/files
chmod 777 /var/www/html/drupal/sites/default/files
cp -R /var/www/html/drupal/sites/default/default.settings.php /var/www/html/drupal/sites/default/settings.php
chmod 777 /var/www/html/drupal/sites/default/settings.php

5) go to default directory in that dafault.settings.php    rename to  setting.php
			cp default.settings.php settings.php
6)  open the file and give the data base name , username , password and hostname
                   vi settings.php
          restart the service    
7)  open the browser and select languages and every thing

